<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB04787</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT FURTHER AMENDING COMMONWEALTH ACT NO. 146 OR THE PUBLIC SERVICE ACT, AS AMENDED</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Provides for the transfer of powers and duties of the Public Service Commission to the various administrative agencies of the government according to their respective jurisdictions; 
States that "Public Utility" shall refer to a public service that regularly supplies the public and directly transmits and distributes to the public through a network its commodity or service of public consequence a public utility necessary to the public and a natural monopoly that needs to be regulated when the public interest so requires as determined by Congress; Enumerates and provides for exemptions operations which shall be classified as public utility.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>BELMONTE, FELICIANO JR., BELMONTE, JOSE CHRISTOPHER Y.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2017-01-18</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Deliberated upon by the Mother Committee on 2017-02-07</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-consolidated with House Bills 4389,4468,4501, 4787 and 4996, for refinement by a TWG</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp2. Deliberated by the TWG on 2017-02-21</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-TWG meetings on 02.07.2017 and 02.21.2017</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp3. Measure approved by the Committee on 2017-05-10</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-The substitute bill was approved by the Committee.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp4. Committee Report filed on 2017-05-31</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-Committee Report# 295, substituted by House Bill 5828,
